IntelliJ IDEA Download On Ubuntu

Step1: Open the Terminal (Ctrl + Alt + T) and enter the following command to change the directory
	cd /opt/

Step2: Enter the command given below to extract the IntelliJ IDEA from ~/Downloads directory. If your downloaded file is in any other directory, replace the last parameter by the actual file path
	sudo tar -xvzf ~/Downloads/ideaIU-14.1.2.tar.gz

Open another Terminal (Ctrl + Alt + T) and enter the following command to create a shortcut file for IntelliJ
	gedit intellij-idea.desktop

Step4: In the opened gedit, copy and paste the following text. If your IntelliJ IDEA version is different, according to your version change the 	Exec location the Icon path:
	[Desktop Entry]
	Name=IntelliJ IDEA
	Type=Application
	Exec=/opt/idea-IU-141.713.2/bin/idea.sh
	Terminal=false
	Icon=/opt/idea-IU-141.713.2/bin/idea.png
	Comment=Integrated Development Environment
	NoDisplay=false
	Categories=Development;IDE;
	Name[en]=IntelliJ IDEA
	Name[en_US]=IntelliJ IDEA

Step5: Save and close the gedit

Step6: Enter the following command in the terminal to install the shortcut
	sudo desktop-file-install intellij-idea.desktop




